 Creating a landing page with a hero section and signup form requires HTML, CSS, and possibly JavaScript for interactivity. Here's a simplified example using HTML5, CSS, and Bootstrap for a clean and responsive design.

**HTML (index.html)**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
 <meta charset="UTF-8">
 <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
 <title>Landing Page</title>

 <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
 <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-KyZXEAg3QhqLMpG8r+Knujsl7/1LwhUtw/nuK8HwyzD+DXK/CfkYi0wSnszjUvs" crossorigin="anonymous">

</head>
<body>

 <!-- Hero section -->
 <header class="d-flex flex-column text-center py-5">
   <h1 class="display-1 fw-bold">Welcome to Our Platform!</h1>
   <p class="lead">Join our network today and access exclusive features.</p>
 </header>

 <!-- Signup form -->
 <section class="container mt-5">
   <h2 class="mb-4">Create an Account</h2>
   <form>
     <div class="mb-3">
       <label for="name" class="form-label">Name</label>
       <input type="text" class="form-control" id="name" placeholder="Enter your name">
     </div>
     <div class="mb-3">
       <label for="email" class="form-label">Email address</label>
       <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Enter email">
       <div id="emailHelp" class="form-text">We'll never share your email with anyone else.</div>
     </div>
     <div class="mb-3">
       <label for="password" class="form-label">Password</label>
       <input type="password" class="form-control" id="password" placeholder="Password">
     </div>
     <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
   </form>
 </section>

 <!-- Optionally, include jQuery and Bootstrap's JS bundles -->
 <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
 <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@popperjs/core@2.11.6/dist/umd/popper.min.js" integrity="sha384-oBqDVmMz4fnFO9gybBud6DZLaM50ctP0sfcXgRsl1J+LrAzG5bHH2IwibRuneE6Wu" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
 <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-cn7l7gDp0eyniUwwAZgrzD06kc/tftFf19TOAs2zVinnD/C7E91j9yyk5FAmoFQ" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

</body>
</html>
```

In the provided example, the landing page consists of a hero section with a header containing the site's title and welcoming message, followed by a signup form. The signup form includes fields for the user's name, email address, and password, and a submit button. The form uses Bootstrap's CSS for styling, and the example also includes the necessary JavaScript files to make the form functional. You can customize the design and functionality as needed to create your perfect landing page.